For data on reference years prior to 2014, please see table 16100045.
All values in this table are rounded to thousand of cubic meters. Therefore, 0.0 quantities do not necessarily mean that there is no economic activity taking place.

In January 2019, a number of changes were made to the questionnaire, the sampling, and the estimation methods for the Monthly Sawmills Survey. The questionnaire was modified to obtain data on shipments of lumber for each species of wood. Data from January 2014 to December 2018 are statistically modelled.
Total softwood includes spruce, pine, fir, Douglas fir, western larch, western hemlock, amabilis fir, western red cedar and all other softwood not elsewhere specified.
Spruce, pine and fir includes all species of spruce (except Sitka spruce), lodgepole pine, jack pine, balsam fir and subalpine fir.
Hemlock fir includes western hemlock, pacific coast hemlock, amabilis fir.
Other softwood includes red pine, ponderosa pine, western and eastern white pine, eastern white cedar, Sitka spruce, yellow cedar or yellow cypress, eastern hemlock, and tamarack or larch.
This represents North American Product Classification System codes 24112, excluding code 2411211
